        description: "CDG Airport is just 25 min from Chelles via the Francilienne and A1.",
        routeDescription: "Via the Francilienne (A104) then A1 north to Roissy.",
        introduction: "The taxi transfer from Chelles to Charles de Gaulle Airport is particularly advantageous thanks to geography: just 25 km separates this historic Marne-side town from France's largest and busiest airport. Chelles, with its 54,000 residents, sits in an ideal position between Paris (22 km to the west) and Roissy (25 km to the north), making it an excellent residential base for frequent travellers and airport-zone professionals. The town's heritage is exceptional -- the Royal Abbey of Chelles, founded in the 7th century by Queen Bathilde, was one of the most important Merovingian monasteries in the Frankish kingdom. Despite CDG's proximity, no direct public transport connection exists from Chelles. Reaching the airport by train requires taking Transilien Line E into Paris Gare de l'Est, then crossing the city to Gare du Nord and boarding the RER B to Roissy -- a journey of at least 1 hour 15 minutes with one or two connections through some of the capital's busiest stations. The taxi bypasses all of this, providing a direct 25-minute transfer via the Francilienne (A104) orbital motorway without ever entering Paris. CDG handles all of France's long-haul flights -- to North America, Asia, Africa, the Middle East and beyond -- making this quick, affordable transfer invaluable.",
