        conseils: "CDG is France's main long-haul hub, with Air France based in Terminals 2E and 2F, Star Alliance carriers at Terminal 1, and budget airlines at Terminal 3. The great advantage for Chelles residents is that the Francilienne provides access to CDG without crossing Paris at all. For long-haul intercontinental flights, plan to depart Chelles approximately 3 hours before your scheduled takeoff. The free CDGVAL automated shuttle connects all terminals within the airport. CDG long-stay parking costs 25-40 euros per day, which means a taxi return trip pays for itself on a weekend away for just two passengers. Before your departure, the Royal Abbey archaeological site and the Musee Alfred-Bonno are well worth a visit, and the nearby Vaires-Torcy Olympic venue offers activities year-round.",
